Marysville.Marysville Getchell High School:
Marysville Getchell High School is a public high school in Marysville, Washington, United States. It is part of the Marysville School District.
The campus has a student capacity of 1,600 in grades 9-12 and is organized into four small learning communities (SLCs): the Academy of Construction and Engineering (ACE), the BioMed Academy (BIO), the International School of Communications (ISC), and the School for the Entrepreneur (SFE).
